{
  "text": "Bulked segregant RNA-seq (BSR-Seq), as a new powerful tool, provides an efficient method to rapidly and efficiently map QTL or genes responsive to stresses including waterlogging. Bulked segregant analysis (BSA) can be used to identify markers linked to any specific gene or genomic region using two bulked DNA sample pools. Each pool, or bulk, contains individuals that are identical in a particular trait or genomic region but arbitrary at all unlinked regions [CITATION_1] . BSA has been extended to bulked sample analysis that can use samples with extreme phenotypes collected from any populations [CITATION_2] . The genetic linkage between markers and genes of interest is determined by quantification of allelic frequencies of genetic markers between the two pools (bulks) of plants [CITATION_3] . Next-generation sequencing (NGS) provides another powerful means to identify SNPs, the most abundant class of markers, in the genome, in order to reveal candidate mutations in the linkage region that may be causal to the phenotype [CITATION_4] . However, for complex traits involving many genes each with minor effect and affected significantly by environments, BSA may not be effective [CITATION_5] . With the advancement of NGS, RNA sequencing technology is combined with BSA to develop BSA RNA-seq (BSR-seq). BSR-seq possesses the advantage of BSA and RNA-seq together. It has the full capability to identify differentially expressed genes (DEGs), and also the ability to identify SNPs different between the pools . BSR-seq has been successfully applied in plants and animals [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . For example, 1,255 DEGs and 56,419 SNPs residing on 4,304 unique genes between susceptible and resistant catfish were identified by BSR-seq . The maize glossy mutants exhibit alterations in the accumulation of epicuticular waxes. Two genes, glossy3 and glossy13, were also identified by the BSR-seq approach [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . Melon fruit flesh color is associated with Orange (CmOr) allelic variation. The regulatory network of CmOr was identified by BSR-seq [CITATION_12] .",
